    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Overall plans, usually graphic and drawn on a small scale, into which the details of other specific plans are fitted. A master plan is frequently supplemented by written material. For plans having to do with land use control law, zoning, and urban redevelopment used to describe the omnibus plans of cities or towns for housing, industry, commercial, and recreational facilities and their impact on environmental factors, use "comprehensive plans".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046959/Bucher, Dictionary of Building Preservation (1996)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000010771/Harris, Dictionary of Architecture and Construction (1993)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>En general, planos en los que se indican los detalles y otros planos específicos.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Globale, veelomvattende ontwerpen, vaak grafisch weergegeven op kleine schaal, waarin de details van andere, specifieke ontwerpen worden ingepast. Een masterplan wordt dikwijls aangevuld door geschreven materiaal. Gebruik 'ruimtelijke ordening' voor ontwerpen die betrekking hebben op wetten die bepalen hoe land wordt gebruikt, ruimtelijke ordening en stadsvernieuwing, als beschrijving voor de overkoepelende plannen van steden voor huisvesting, industriële, commerciële en recreatieve faciliteiten en de invloed daarvan op het milieu.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052374/Polytechnisch woordenboek En-Ne (1991)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Gesamtplan, meist graphisch und in kleinem Maßstab gezeichnet, in dem die Details anderer spezifischer Pläne zusammen gefasst sind. Ein Masterplan wird oft ergänzt durch geschriebenes Material. Für Pläne, die mit dem Flächennutzungskontrollgesetz, mit der Aufstellung eines Flächennutzungsplans und städtischer Sanierung, die Omnibuspläne von Städten oder Ortschaften für die Bebauungs-, Industrie-, Handel- und Freizeitangelegenheiten und ihren Einfluss auf Umweltfaktoren beschreiben, zu tun haben, wird “Bauleitplan” verwendet.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>整體的規劃圖，通常以小型的圖解形式繪製，並納入其他特定規劃的細節。主規劃圖通常附有書面資料作為說明。至於與土地使用管制法、都市區域劃分以及都市更新有關的規劃圖，用於描述城鎮住宅、工業、商業及娛樂設施區及其對環境因子影響的概括規劃，則使用「綜合規劃」一詞。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Plantas gerais, geralmente desenhos em uma escala pequena nos quais os detalhes de outras plantas específicas fazem parte. Uma planta mestre é normalmente complementada com um material escrito. Para plantas relacionadas às leis de controle de uso de terra, zoneamento e redesenvolvimento urbano usado para descrever plantas de ônibus de cidades ou condições para casas, indústrias, instalações recreativas e seu impacto nos fatores ambientais, use "plantas completas".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000179/VP-intern</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000110648/Portuguese Translation Intern Project (2020-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
